operation.name: POST
operation.documentation:
Creates a new data store on file-share. A data store represents a hosting device providing storage for object services. The file share CoS included in the request determines the class of file-device used to create the file-share for this data store creation request.

Note that the data store creation is an asynchronous operation, so a successful invocation of this request does not necessarily mean that the creation has completed.
operation.tag: Virtual pool has to be created

inValue.documentation: Parameters necessary for the data store creation, such as size and file share CoS.

operation.name: POST
operation.documentation:
Creates a new data store on NFS-Server. A data store represents a hosting device providing storage for object services. In case of NFS-Server creation, the hosting device CoS is determined by the NFS export provided.

Note that the data store creation is an asynchronous operation, so a successful invocation of this request does not necessarily mean that the creation has completed.
operation.tag: Virtual pool has to be created

inValue.documentation: Parameters necessary for the data store creation, such as size and mount point.
